MariaDb setup steps:
1. login to Synology with SSH after installing the MariaDb
Example cmd: ssh 192.168.2.2
2. login
3. move to /usr/local/mariadb10/bin
Example cmd: cd /usr/local/mariadb10/bin
4. execute command: ./mysql -u root -p
5. enter the root password you gave during MariaDb installation
6. Execute the below commands, by changing the username and password (might be also the ip) to the correct ones:
(Note: ' ' signs must remain!)
CREATE USER 'username'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'username'@'localhost' WITH GRANT OPTION;

CREATE USER 'username'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'username'@'%' WITH GRANT OPTION;

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

7. Once done with all four queries, it should connect with the given username and password